<div id="review_2738928715" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2738928715" />
    <a title="Ryan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/64585245-ryan"><img alt="Ryan" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/images/nophoto/user/c_111x148.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2738928715?book_show_action=true">Mar 14, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ryan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ryan" href="/user/show/64585245-ryan">Ryan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780440245872" href="/book/show/6466878-firefly-summer">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2738928715" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13877660184742661796">A more tightly focused novel from Maeve Binchy, similar to Circle of Friends in that sense. Transporting readers to the mid-century Irish village of Mountfern, Binchy&apos;s book spins a web about the uncertainties of living, family, growing up, love, and finding a home. Concentrated with Binchy&apos;s trademark combination of humor and sadness, Firefly Summer keeps readers engaged with the quotidian but never dull lives of Irish village life.</span>
  <span id="freeText13877660184742661796" style="display:none">A more tightly focused novel from Maeve Binchy, similar to Circle of Friends in that sense. Transporting readers to the mid-century Irish village of Mountfern, Binchy's book spins a web about the uncertainties of living, family, growing up, love, and finding a home. Concentrated with Binchy's trademark combination of humor and sadness, Firefly Summer keeps readers engaged with the quotidian but never dull lives of Irish village life.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13877660184742661796" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
