<span id="freeTextContainer17736151058056187954">It saddens me to know that we as readers have lost a truly fantastic storyteller when Maeve Binchy died this year. So many hours of my life have been spent truly swept up into the characters and stories she has written. <br/>Firefly Summer was one of her earlier works that I had nt ben able to locate an audio version until recently. This 788 pg bok is Maeve Binchy at her best with multi-faceted characters and a saga of a story you don&apos;t want to end. Reading Firefly Summer was like being so held capti</span>
  <span id="freeText17736151058056187954" style="display:none">It saddens me to know that we as readers have lost a truly fantastic storyteller when Maeve Binchy died this year. So many hours of my life have been spent truly swept up into the characters and stories she has written. <br />Firefly Summer was one of her earlier works that I had nt ben able to locate an audio version until recently. This 788 pg bok is Maeve Binchy at her best with multi-faceted characters and a saga of a story you don't want to end. Reading Firefly Summer was like being so held captive by the tune and lyrics of an Irish ballad that you could picture yourself in the story. <br />If you've never read anything by Maeve Binchy, you are missing a reading pleasure of the highest quality, if you like "slice of life" fiction written by a gifted irish storyteller! <br /><br />Thank you Maeve for sharing your beautiful storytelling gift and yourself with all your devoted fans. We will miss you! We'll be recommending your books for manay, many years to come, so the gift will live on! </span>
